# Architecture — Seven Pillars

Every implementation decision must align with these pillars. If a design choice conflicts with a pillar, the pillar wins.

## 1. Decomposition Is the Architecture
- Quality → 5 independent dimensions (Clarity, Value Prop, CTA, Brand Voice, Emotional Resonance)
- Brand voice → audience-specific profiles (parent-facing, student-facing)
- Ad structure → combinable atoms (hook type, body pattern, CTA style, tone register)
- Evaluation → forced chain-of-thought decomposition before scoring
- Visual consistency (v2) → attribute checklists, not holistic judgment

## 2. Prevention Over Detection Over Correction
- Grounded brief expansion prevents hallucinated product claims
- Shared semantic briefs prevent multi-modal incoherence (v2)
- Tiered compliance (prompt + evaluator + regex) prevents policy violations
- Pareto-optimal selection prevents dimension collapse
- Every dollar spent on prevention saves ten on detection

## 3. Every Token Is an Investment, Not an Expense
- Tiered model routing: Flash for drafts, Pro only for improvable-range ads (5.5–7.0)
- Full token attribution with marginal analysis per pipeline stage
- Result-level caching with version-based TTL
- Contrastive rationales reduce regeneration cycles
- Performance-decay-triggered exploration — explore only when exploit is exhausted

## 4. The System Knows What It Doesn't Know
- Confidence scores on every evaluation (feeds human escalation)
- Statistical process control for evaluator drift detection
- Inversion tests + correlation analysis prove dimension independence
- Confidence-gated autonomy: >7 autonomous, 5–7 flagged, <5 human required

## 5. State Is Sacred
- Checkpoint-and-resume: every successful API call writes a checkpoint
- Append-only decision ledger (JSONL): no data ever lost or modified
- Per-ad deterministic seed chains: `seed = hash(global_seed + brief_id + cycle_number)`
- Full input-output snapshots for forensic reproducibility

## 6. Learning Is Structural
- Reference-decompose-recombine: proven ad patterns → structural atoms → recombination
- Single-variable isolation for A/B variants (change one element, measure impact)
- Shared structural patterns across campaigns; content stays campaign-specific

## 7. Visible Reasoning Is a First-Class Output
- Narrated pipeline replay: chronological walkthrough with reasoning and failures
- Contrastive evaluation rationales: "what this ad is" vs "what +2 would look like"
- Decision log documents OPTIONS CONSIDERED, choice, and WHY — not just what was done

## Directory Structure

```
generate/       — Ad copy generation from expanded briefs
evaluate/       — Chain-of-thought dimension scoring, LLM-as-Judge, aggregation
iterate/        — Feedback loop, brief mutation, Pareto selection, quality ratchet
output/         — Formatting, export, quality trends, narrated replay
data/           — Brand knowledge base, reference ads, pattern database, config
tests/          — Golden set, adversarial, inversion, correlation tests
docs/           — Decision log, limitations, technical writeup
```

## Pipeline Flow

```
Brief → Expand (grounded) → Generate (reference-decompose-recombine)
  → Evaluate (CoT 5-step) → Above threshold?
  ├─ Yes → Published library
  └─ No  → Weakest dimension → Contrastive rationale
           → Pareto regeneration (3–5 variants) → Re-evaluate
           → After 2 failures: mutate brief → After 3: escalate
```

## Model Routing

| Task | Model | Rationale |
|------|-------|-----------|
| First-draft generation + initial scoring | Gemini Flash | 80% of work at lowest cost |
| Regeneration for improvable ads (5.5–7.0) | Gemini Pro | Quality tokens on borderline ads |
| Brief expansion + context distillation | Gemini Flash | Cheap LLM call, high ROI |
| Image generation (v2) | Imagen / Flux | Brand-consistent visuals |
